---
import StaticArticlePage from '@/components/ui/StaticArticlePage.astro'
import { getLegalContactLinks } from '@/lib/legal-contact'
import { getTermsHref } from '@/lib/terms-links'

const { legalEmail, supportEmail } = getLegalContactLinks()
const contactEmails = [legalEmail, supportEmail].filter((email) => email !== null)
---

<StaticArticlePage
  description="Terms for using SeniorPath and related services operated by Fengsoft."
  englishHref={getTermsHref('en')}
  kicker="Legal"
  portugueseHref={getTermsHref('pt-br')}
  title="Terms of Service"
>
  <p>
    These Terms of Service govern your access to and use of SeniorPath and any related websites, newsletters,
    tools, content, products, and services we make available through it.
  </p>

  <h2>Who operates SeniorPath</h2>
  <p>
    SeniorPath is operated by FENGSOFT SERVICOS EM TECNOLOGIA E EDUCACAO LTDA, CNPJ 43.257.394/0001-70,
    based in Niteroi, Rio de Janeiro, Brazil. In these terms, "SeniorPath", "we", "our", and "us" refer to
    Fengsoft and the SeniorPath project.
  </p>

  <h2>What SeniorPath is</h2>
  <p>
    SeniorPath is an editorial learning platform focused on senior-level engineering judgment. It may publish
    guides, concepts, glossary entries, topic hubs, learning paths, newsletters, and other educational or
    product-related content.
  </p>
  <p>
    Today, some parts of SeniorPath may be available for free without an account. Over time, we may add
    accounts, comments, downloads, community features, premium content, software tools, SaaS products,
    consulting offers, or other services operated by Fengsoft.
  </p>

  <h2>Acceptance of these terms</h2>
  <p>
    By accessing or using SeniorPath, you agree to these Terms of Service and any additional terms or policies
    that apply to specific features, products, or services. If you do not agree, do not use SeniorPath.
  </p>

  <h2>Who may use SeniorPath</h2>
  <p>
    You may use SeniorPath only if you can legally enter into a binding agreement under applicable law. If you
    use SeniorPath on behalf of a company or organization, you represent that you have authority to bind that
    entity to these terms.
  </p>

  <h2>Permitted use</h2>
  <p>
    You may use SeniorPath for personal learning, professional development, internal team discussion, and
    lawful business use.
  </p>
  <p>
    You may not:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>break, disable, overload, reverse engineer, or interfere with the platform or its security</li>
    <li>scrape, harvest, or extract content in an abusive, automated, or unauthorized way</li>
    <li>republish, mirror, resell, or redistribute substantial portions of the content as your own</li>
    <li>use SeniorPath to build a competing content database, training set, or commercial knowledge product without permission</li>
    <li>submit spam, malware, misleading content, or unlawful material</li>
    <li>impersonate another person or misrepresent your affiliation with a business or brand</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Accounts and subscriptions</h2>
  <p>
    Some features may require you to subscribe, submit your email address, or create an account. You agree to
    provide accurate information and to keep your access credentials secure if accounts are introduced.
  </p>
  <p>
    We may suspend or restrict access to accounts, subscriptions, or features if we reasonably believe there is
    abuse, fraud, unlawful activity, or a violation of these terms.
  </p>

  <h2>Newsletters and communications</h2>
  <p>
    If you subscribe to a newsletter or other communications, you agree that we may send editorial updates,
    product news, service announcements, and promotional communications related to SeniorPath, Fengsoft, Capta,
    and other current or future products or services.
  </p>
  <p>
    You can unsubscribe from non-essential marketing emails at any time using the unsubscribe link included in
    the message.
  </p>

  <h2>Products, services, and promotions</h2>
  <p>
    SeniorPath may promote or offer products, software, SaaS tools, templates, consulting, educational offers,
    or other services operated by Fengsoft. Some parts of the site may also include sponsored content, partner
    placements, affiliate links, or advertising.
  </p>
  <p>
    Additional terms, pricing pages, order forms, trial terms, or product-specific conditions may apply to paid
    offers. If there is a conflict, the more specific terms for that product or service will control.
  </p>

  <h2>Intellectual property</h2>
  <p>
    Unless otherwise stated, SeniorPath and its content, including text, structure, branding, graphics, site
    design, and original materials, are owned by Fengsoft or its licensors and are protected by applicable
    intellectual property laws.
  </p>
  <p>
    You may share links to SeniorPath and reference limited excerpts with proper attribution. You may not copy,
    reproduce, republish, distribute, or commercially exploit substantial portions of the site without prior
    written permission.
  </p>

  <h2>Feedback and submissions</h2>
  <p>
    If you send feedback, suggestions, ideas, or similar submissions, you grant us a non-exclusive,
    worldwide, royalty-free license to use, adapt, publish, and improve upon that feedback for SeniorPath,
    Capta, and our related products and services, without compensation to you.
  </p>

  <h2>No professional advice</h2>
  <p>
    SeniorPath is an educational and editorial resource. Its content is provided for general information and
    learning only. It is not legal, financial, tax, security, hiring, medical, or business advice for your
    specific situation.
  </p>
  <p>
    You are responsible for how you interpret and apply anything you read on the site.
  </p>

  <h2>Third-party services and links</h2>
  <p>
    SeniorPath may link to third-party websites or use third-party services such as analytics providers, email
    platforms, payment processors, embedded media, or comment systems. Those third parties operate under their
    own terms and privacy practices, and we are not responsible for how they operate.
  </p>

  <h2>Availability and changes</h2>
  <p>
    We may update, change, suspend, rename, limit, or discontinue any part of SeniorPath at any time, with or
    without notice. We may also update these Terms of Service from time to time. The updated version becomes
    effective when it is published on the site, unless a different date is stated.
  </p>

  <h2>Disclaimer of warranties</h2>
  <p>
    SeniorPath is provided on an "as is" and "as available" basis. To the maximum extent permitted by law, we
    make no warranties or guarantees that the site will always be available, accurate, complete, secure, or fit
    for a particular purpose.
  </p>

  <h2>Limitation of liability</h2>
  <p>
    To the maximum extent permitted by applicable law, Fengsoft and SeniorPath will not be liable for any
    indirect, incidental, special, consequential, or punitive damages, or for loss of profits, revenue, data,
    goodwill, or business opportunities arising out of or related to your use of, or inability to use,
    SeniorPath.
  </p>
  <p>
    This includes losses resulting from decisions made based on content, downtime, third-party services, or
    unauthorized access, except where liability cannot be excluded under applicable law.
  </p>

  <h2>Privacy</h2>
  <p>
    We may process personal data in connection with SeniorPath, including newsletter subscriptions, analytics,
    contact requests, and product inquiries. Our data handling practices are described in our Privacy Policy and
    must be interpreted together with these terms.
  </p>

  <h2>Governing law and venue</h2>
  <p>
    These terms are governed by the laws of Brazil. Unless mandatory law provides otherwise, disputes relating to
    these terms or to SeniorPath will be submitted to the courts of Niteroi, Rio de Janeiro, Brazil.
  </p>

  {contactEmails.length > 0 ? (
    <>
      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        For legal questions, support requests, or notices related to these terms, contact us at{' '}
        {contactEmails.map((email, index) => (
          <>
            {index > 0 ? (index === contactEmails.length - 1 ? ' or ' : ', ') : null}
            <a href={email.href}>{email.value}</a>
          </>
        ))}
        .
      </p>
    </>
  ) : null}
</StaticArticlePage>
